{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vx13iQNUkqvAVxCfoXefzB","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"OpenMC official data libraries ENDF/B-VIII.0 HDF5 download tar.xz direct link\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Cross sections - OpenMC\",\"url\":\"https://openmc.org/data/\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - openmc-data-storage/ENDF-B-VIII.0-NNDC-json: A collection of json file for each nuclide and reaction in the nuclear data library · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/openmc-data-storage/ENDF-B-VIII.0-NNDC-json\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - openmc-dev/data: Collection of scripts for managing data for OpenMC · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/openmc-dev/data\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - openmc-data-storage/openmc_data: Python package for processing nuclear data distribution in ACE and ENDF format into HDF5 format for use in OpenMC. Adapted from the openmc data repo. · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/openmc-data-storage/openmc_data\"},{\"title\":\"ENDF/B-VIII.0 HDF5 library for OpenMC with cross sections at 20 K\",\"url\":\"https://zenodo.org/records/8410375\"},{\"title\":\"openmc-data · PyPI\",\"url\":\"https://pypi.org/project/openmc-data/0.0.2/\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) Nuclear data processing capabilities in OpenMC\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/319672958_Nuclear_data_processing_capabilities_in_OpenMC\"},{\"title\":\"openmc-data-downloader · PyPI\",\"url\":\"https://pypi.org/project/openmc-data-downloader/\"},{\"title\":\"Nuclear Data — OpenMC Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.openmc.org/en/v0.11.0/examples/nuclear-data.html\"},{\"title\":\"3. Cross Section Configuration — OpenMC Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.openmc.org/en/v0.12.1/usersguide/cross_sections.html\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found relevant information about OpenMC official data libraries for ENDF/B-VIII.0 in HDF5 format:\n\n## Key Findings:\n\nThe official library includes incident neutron, photoatomic, atomic relaxation, and thermal scattering data from ENDF/B-VIII.0. This library was produced by converting ACE files from the Lib80x and ENDF80SaB2 libraries that were generated by the Nuclear Data Team at LANL. Incident neutron data is available at seven temperatures: 0.1 K, 250 K, 293.6 K, 600 K, 900 K, 1200 K, and 2500 K.\n\n## Download Options:\n\nThe primary source for pregenerated HDF5 libraries is:\n- Most of the pregenerated HDF5 libraries are available at https://openmc.org\n\nAdditionally, there's a documented direct download link from a GitHub repository:\n- A direct download link is available at https://anl.box.com/shared/static/uhbxlrx7hvxqw27psymfbhi7bx7s6u6a.xz for the ENDF/B-VIII.0 tar.xz archive\n\nThe official OpenMC data page at https://openmc.org/data/ provides access to all available pregenerated HDF5 libraries in various formats including tar.xz archives.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"9f296a9e-295d-47c7-b9e2-bf89bcd19323","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:08:45.338Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"OpenMC official data libraries ENDF/B-VIII.0 HDF5 download tar.xz direct link","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01D6yutt2dXuUFm2aAYDmQnR","content":[{"title":"Cross sections - OpenMC","url":"https://openmc.org/data/"},{"title":"GitHub - openmc-data-storage/ENDF-B-VIII.0-NNDC-json: A collection of json file for each nuclide and reaction in the nuclear data library · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/openmc-data-storage/ENDF-B-VIII.0-NNDC-json"},{"title":"GitHub - openmc-dev/data: Collection of scripts for managing data for OpenMC · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/openmc-dev/data"},{"title":"GitHub - openmc-data-storage/openmc_data: Python package for processing nuclear data distribution in ACE and ENDF format into HDF5 format for use in OpenMC. Adapted from the openmc data repo. · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/openmc-data-storage/openmc_data"},{"title":"ENDF/B-VIII.0 HDF5 library for OpenMC with cross sections at 20 K","url":"https://zenodo.org/records/8410375"},{"title":"openmc-data · PyPI","url":"https://pypi.org/project/openmc-data/0.0.2/"},{"title":"(PDF) Nuclear data processing capabilities in OpenMC","url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/319672958_Nuclear_data_processing_capabilities_in_OpenMC"},{"title":"openmc-data-downloader · PyPI","url":"https://pypi.org/project/openmc-data-downloader/"},{"title":"Nuclear Data — OpenMC Documentation","url":"https://docs.openmc.org/en/v0.11.0/examples/nuclear-data.html"},{"title":"3. Cross Section Configuration — OpenMC Documentation","url":"https://docs.openmc.org/en/v0.12.1/usersguide/cross_sections.html"}]},"Based on the search results, I found relevant information about OpenMC official data libraries for ENDF/B-VIII.0 in HDF5 format:\n\n## Key Findings:\n\nThe official library includes incident neutron, photoatomic, atomic relaxation, and thermal scattering data from ENDF/B-VIII.0. This library was produced by converting ACE files from the Lib80x and ENDF80SaB2 libraries that were generated by the Nuclear Data Team at LANL. Incident neutron data is available at seven temperatures: 0.1 K, 250 K, 293.6 K, 600 K, 900 K, 1200 K, and 2500 K.\n\n## Download Options:\n\nThe primary source for pregenerated HDF5 libraries is:\n- Most of the pregenerated HDF5 libraries are available at https://openmc.org\n\nAdditionally, there's a documented direct download link from a GitHub repository:\n- A direct download link is available at https://anl.box.com/shared/static/uhbxlrx7hvxqw27psymfbhi7bx7s6u6a.xz for the ENDF/B-VIII.0 tar.xz archive\n\nThe official OpenMC data page at https://openmc.org/data/ provides access to all available pregenerated HDF5 libraries in various formats including tar.xz archives."],"durationSeconds":6.906921879000001,"searchCount":1}}
