{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01AWnrsut9xpJccXkhXtKwtW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Collect HTTR design data","prompt":"I am building a neutronics + thermal model of the HTTR (High Temperature Engineering Test Reactor, JAEA/JAERI, Japan — a 30 MWt prismatic graphite-moderated helium-cooled HTGR). I need you to collect PUBLIC DESIGN DATA and give me specific numbers with citations (URL + what the number is).\n\nCRITICAL HARD RULE — you MUST obey: Only consult DESIGN / engineering / neutronics-design publications. You MUST NOT search for, open, read, or report anything about the HTTR \"loss-of-forced-cooling\" (LOFC) test, \"loss of forced cooling\", circulator-trip test, \"safety demonstration test\" RESULTS, measured recriticality times, measured power traces, or measured temperature transients. Do not open any paper/page whose title or abstract indicates it reports those test results. If a design source you open contains such results, stop reading it, do not report those numbers, and note the incident. Stick to steady-state design specs.\n\nPlease find and report, each with a citation URL and a one-line note:\n\nCORE GEOMETRY\n- Thermal power, coolant inlet/outlet temperatures, He pressure, He mass flow rate at full power.\n- Active core: equivalent diameter, active height, number of fuel columns, number of stacked fuel blocks per column, number of control rod columns, reflector columns.\n- Hexagonal fuel block: width across flats, height.\n- Fuel rod (\"pin-in-block\"): number of fuel rods per block, fuel rod outer diameter, coolant channel diameter, pitch.\n\nFUEL\n- Fuel compact geometry: outer diameter, inner diameter (annular?), height, number of compacts per rod.\n- TRISO particle: UO2 kernel diameter, buffer/IPyC/SiC/OPyC layer thicknesses and densities, TRISO packing fraction in the compact.\n- Enrichment zoning: number of enrichment zones, min/max/core-average U-235 wt% enrichment, how zones are arranged.\n- Burnable poison: composition (B4C?), location, loading.\n\nMATERIALS / THERMAL\n- Graphite grades used (fuel block matrix, fuel compact matrix, reflector) and their densities.\n- Boron/impurity content of the graphite (natural boron equivalent, ppm) — important for neutronics.\n- Total mass of graphite in the core (or enough to estimate it), graphite specific heat capacity vs temperature.\n- Reflector thickness (top/bottom/radial), reflector material.\n- Vessel Cooling System (VCS): its heat removal capacity (kW or MW), how it couples to the core/vessel.\n- Kinetics parameters if published: delayed neutron fraction beta_eff, prompt neutron lifetime.\n\nPrioritize authoritative sources: IAEA TECDOC (e.g. TECDOC-1382, 1163, 1249), JAERI/JAEA design reports, Nuclear Engineering and Design papers by Saito, Fujimoto, Nakagawa, Takamatsu, Shiozawa on HTTR design and core physics, and the IAEA HTTR benchmark design specifications. Give me the actual numbers, organized under the headings above. Be thorough and precise with units.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":518,"cache_read_input_tokens":45091,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":518},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"c65eeb43-4dee-42fc-a407-c3077e4cb917","request_id":"req_011CcdzekrzBKS7CygQTLkGh"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"adb4b4102b222af1b","tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","description":"Collect HTTR design data","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"I am building a neutronics + thermal model of the HTTR (High Temperature Engineering Test Reactor, JAEA/JAERI, Japan — a 30 MWt prismatic graphite-moderated helium-cooled HTGR). I need you to collect PUBLIC DESIGN DATA and give me specific numbers with citations (URL + what the number is).\n\nCRITICAL HARD RULE — you MUST obey: Only consult DESIGN / engineering / neutronics-design publications. You MUST NOT search for, open, read, or report anything about the HTTR \"loss-of-forced-cooling\" (LOFC) test, \"loss of forced cooling\", circulator-trip test, \"safety demonstration test\" RESULTS, measured recriticality times, measured power traces, or measured temperature transients. Do not open any paper/page whose title or abstract indicates it reports those test results. If a design source you open contains such results, stop reading it, do not report those numbers, and note the incident. Stick to steady-state design specs.\n\nPlease find and report, each with a citation URL and a one-line note:\n\nCORE GEOMETRY\n- Thermal power, coolant inlet/outlet temperatures, He pressure, He mass flow rate at full power.\n- Active core: equivalent diameter, active height, number of fuel columns, number of stacked fuel blocks per column, number of control rod columns, reflector columns.\n- Hexagonal fuel block: width across flats, height.\n- Fuel rod (\"pin-in-block\"): number of fuel rods per block, fuel rod outer diameter, coolant channel diameter, pitch.\n\nFUEL\n- Fuel compact geometry: outer diameter, inner diameter (annular?), height, number of compacts per rod.\n- TRISO particle: UO2 kernel diameter, buffer/IPyC/SiC/OPyC layer thicknesses and densities, TRISO packing fraction in the compact.\n- Enrichment zoning: number of enrichment zones, min/max/core-average U-235 wt% enrichment, how zones are arranged.\n- Burnable poison: composition (B4C?), location, loading.\n\nMATERIALS / THERMAL\n- Graphite grades used (fuel block matrix, fuel compact matrix, reflector) and their densities.\n- Boron/impurity content of the graphite (natural boron equivalent, ppm) — important for neutronics.\n- Total mass of graphite in the core (or enough to estimate it), graphite specific heat capacity vs temperature.\n- Reflector thickness (top/bottom/radial), reflector material.\n- Vessel Cooling System (VCS): its heat removal capacity (kW or MW), how it couples to the core/vessel.\n- Kinetics parameters if published: delayed neutron fraction beta_eff, prompt neutron lifetime.\n\nPrioritize authoritative sources: IAEA TECDOC (e.g. TECDOC-1382, 1163, 1249), JAERI/JAEA design reports, Nuclear Engineering and Design papers by Saito, Fujimoto, Nakagawa, Takamatsu, Shiozawa on HTTR design and core physics, and the IAEA HTTR benchmark design specifications. Give me the actual numbers, organized under the headings above. Be thorough and precise with units.","uuid":"1a927af7-c8ca-47b0-9e5a-73812b3cbf24","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e"}
