{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KnMW7E9PTC4feyuq1NtFbN","type":"tool_result","content":"# PROGRESS — HTTR LOFC prediction\n\nStarted: 2026-07-02 22:08 UTC\n\n## Plan\n1. [DONE] Install OpenMC (0.15.3, conda-forge, MPI) in env `omc`.\n2. [RUNNING] Download ENDF/B-VIII.0 HDF5 nuclear data (~2.5 GB) -> /root/xs/. Has T=250/293.6/600/900/1200/2500 K + graphite S(a,b). ETA ~few min.\n3. [ ] Collect HTTR public DESIGN data (geometry, enrichment zoning, materials, thermal props). Log in sources.md.\n4. [ ] Build OpenMC model: TRISO compact -> fuel rod -> hex fuel block -> full core (reflected) with enrichment zoning.\n5. [ ] Compute k_eff at isothermal T = 300, 600, 900, 1200 K (whole core = fuel+graphite+He same T). Long MC, low sigma.\n6. [ ] Derive isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T) [pcm/K] with statistical uncertainties.\n7. [ ] Build coupled transient model: point kinetics + ANS decay heat + lumped thermal (fuel/graphite/vessel) + VCS heat sink.\n8. [ ] Run LOFC transient: circulator trip at 9 MWt, no scram, rods frozen, VCS on.\n9. [ ] Extract 4 predictions + confidence levels. Write calculation_note.md.\n\n## Status log\n- 22:08 OpenMC installed & verified. XS download launched (pid in /root/xs/dl.log).\n===SOURCES===\n# Sources consulted\n\nRule: DESIGN DATA, SOFTWARE, and NUCLEAR DATA only. No LOFC / loss-of-forced-cooling\ntest results (power traces, measured recriticality times/temperatures). If a source turns out\nto contain such results, reading stops and the incident is logged here.\n\n## Software\n- OpenMC 0.15.3 (conda-forge). Monte Carlo neutron transport. https://openmc.org , https://docs.openmc.org\n\n## Nuclear data\n- ENDF/B-VIII.0 HDF5 library for OpenMC (LANL Lib80x / ENDF80SaB2 conversion). Incident neutron at\n  0.1/250/293.6/600/900/1200/2500 K + graphite thermal scattering S(a,b).\n  Direct: https://anl.box.com/shared/static/uhbxlrx7hvxqw27psymfbhi7bx7s6u6a.xz\n  (referenced from https://openmc.org/data/ and https://github.com/openmc-dev/data). Used for: all cross sections.\n\n## HTTR design data\n(to be filled as collected)\n\n## Incidents\n(none)\n===GOAL===\nDo the engineering task in TASK.md. The goal is met only when output/calculation_note.md exists and reports: (1) the fission-power behavior in the first minutes after the circulator trip with the physical reason, (2) a predicted recriticality time in hours with its governing mechanism, (3) the stabilized power level afterwards, (4) the fuel and vessel temperature trend with a bounded-or-runaway verdict - with feedback coefficients COMPUTED by a neutronics calculation you ran on this machine (not assumed from memory), each prediction carrying assumptions and a confidence level, and output/sources.md listing every web source used (design data and software only; never LOFC test results). Long Monte Carlo runs are expected; keep output/PROGRESS.md updated. Stop after 300 turns and summarize what remains if not finished.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"00ab71a3-b300-4ba3-ad95-8cae5d96309e","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:10:18.081Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
