{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018GRa9KkpybV7id1e566ZS4","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"HTTR reactor design specifications core geometry fuel block IAEA TECDOC prismatic 30 MWt\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"IAEA-TECDOC-1382 Evaluation of high temperature gas cooled reactor performance:\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/publications/PDF/te_1382_web/TE_1382_Part1.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"IAEA TECDOC SERIES Coated Particle Fuels for High Temperature Gas Cooled\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/publications/PDF/TE-2090web.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"IAEA-TECDOC-899 Design and development of gas cooled reactors with\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/Publications/PDF/te_899_web.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"1944-18 Joint ICTP-IAEA Workshop on Nuclear Reaction Data for Advanced\",\"url\":\"https://indico.ictp.it/event/a07153/session/11/contribution/6/material/0/1.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Evaluation of the HTTR criticality and burnup calculations with continuous-energy and multigroup cross sections - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549313006419\"},{\"title\":\"Proceedings of HTR 2010 Prague, Czech Republic, October 18-20, 2010 Paper 206\",\"url\":\"https://www.ornl.gov/file/development-and-validation-scale-nuclear-analysis-methods-high-temperature-gas-cooled-reactors/display\"},{\"title\":\"High Temperature Gas Cooled Reactor Fuels and Materials\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/Publications/PDF/TE_1645_CD/PDF/TECDOC_1645.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"IAEA-TECDOC-1694 Evaluation of High Temperature\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/Publications/PDF/TE-1694_web.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Nuclear reactor system with lift-out core assembly\",\"url\":\"https://image-ppubs.uspto.gov/dirsearch-public/print/downloadPdf/11610694\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here is information about the HTTR reactor design specifications:\n\n## HTTR Reactor Overview\n\nThe design thermal output of HTTR is 30 MW and the maximum gas outlet temperature could be up to 950 °C. The High Temperature Engineering Test Reactor (HTTR) in Japan is a helium-cooled graphite-moderated prismatic-type reactor.\n\n## Core Geometry\n\nThe core consists of core components which are prismatic hexagonal blocks 580mm in height and 360mm in width across the flats. These include fuel assembly blocks, control rod guide blocks, replaceable reflector blocks, and irradiation blocks.\n\n## Fuel Block Specifications\n\nThe fuel graphite block is a prismatic hexagonal block 580mm in height and 360mm in width across the flats. The block has 33 fuel holes in the fuel zones 1 and 2, and 31 fuel holes in the fuel zone 3 and 4.\n\nThe fuel rod consists of a graphite sleeve containing 14 fuel compacts. It is inserted into the coolant channel of the fuel graphite block. The form is a hollow cylinder of 10mm in inner diameter, 26mm in outer diameter and 39mm in height.\n\n## IAEA Documentation\n\nThe information presented here is sourced from IAEA-TECDOC-1382, which provides comprehensive evaluation of high temperature gas cooled reactor performance, including detailed specifications for the HTTR design.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"ca3f4207-85c3-4ceb-8c04-8df6b8dadbc9","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:10:32.618Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Fq2d182X6hKTVSyVFVeoG7","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"HTTR fuel design TRISO UO2 kernel diameter coating layer thickness enrichment zoning fuel compact\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"HTTR fuel kernel to fuel column schematic. | Download Scientific Diagram\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/HTTR-fuel-kernel-to-fuel-column-schematic_fig4_255217953\"},{\"title\":\"Optimum coating layer thicknesses of a TRISO having an 800-μm UO2 kernel under normal operation conditions of a 10-MWth block-type HTGR - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0029549321002843\"},{\"title\":\"Design and manufacture of the fuel element for the 10 MW ...\",\"url\":\"https://www.gen-4.org/gif/upload/docs/application/pdf/2022-11/design-and-manufacture-of-the-fuel-element-for-the-10_2002_nuclear-engineeri.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"FABRICATION OF HTTR FIRST LOADING FUEL XA0100873\",\"url\":\"https://www.osti.gov/etdeweb/servlets/purl/20158164\"},{\"title\":\"High Temperature Gas Cooled Reactor Fuels and Materials\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/Publications/PDF/TE_1645_CD/PDF/TECDOC_1645.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Fabrication of uranium oxycarbide kernels and compacts for HTR fuel - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S002954931100906X\"},{\"title\":\"Performance Analysis Review of Thorium TRISO Coated ...\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/Publications/PDF/TE-1761_web.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"2-1 2. TRISO-COATED FUEL PARTICLE PERFORMANCE 2.1\",\"url\":\"https://www.nrc.gov/docs/ML0406/ML040650057.pdf\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here is detailed information about HTTR fuel design with TRISO coated particles:\n\n## TRISO Fuel Particle Structure\n\nA coated fuel particle consists of a kernel and four coating layers formed around the kernel by vapor-deposition technology using a fluidized bed type of coater.\n\n## UO2 Kernel Specifications\n\nFor HTTR TRISO fuel types, the fuel kernel has a radius of 300 μm. This corresponds to a kernel diameter of approximately 600 μm.\n\n## Coating Layer Thickness\n\nCoating layers are composed of 60 μm of low-density buffer, 30 μm of high-density PyC, 25 μm of SiC and 45 μm of high-density PyC.\n\n## Enrichment and Zoning\n\nFuel enrichment varies from 3 w/o to 10 w/o, and the density of graphite matrix outside the fuel particles in the fuel compact region is 1.7 g/cm³.\n\n## Fuel Compact Composition\n\nA fuel compact contains about 13,000 coated fuel particles.\n\nThese specifications define the standard HTTR TRISO fuel design used in the High Temperature Test Reactor, providing the detailed dimensional and material parameters for the kernel, coating layers, and overall fuel compact assembly.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"7f3142f5-8f6e-4f38-834a-b6a0683f7582","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:10:33.730Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
