{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015M3b4JDJcLr6ko3sexoYbR","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"HTTR helium mass flow rate 10.2 kg/s coolant pressure 4 MPa inlet 395 outlet 850 950 design\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Preliminary study on HTR-10 operating at higher outlet temperature - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549322003090\"},{\"title\":\"Frontiers | Numerical Investigation of Hot Helium Flow Homogenizer on Inter-Unit Flow Rate Uniformity of HTGR Once Through Steam Generator\",\"url\":\"https://frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fenrg.2022.925380/full\"},{\"title\":\"Design of an Alternative Coolant Inlet Flow Configuaration for the Modular Helium Reactor (Conference) | OSTI.GOV\",\"url\":\"https://osti.gov/biblio/911813-sA3p3H\"},{\"title\":\"Final Design Of The Pre-production SSR2 Cryomodule For PIP-II Project At   Fermilab\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2209.01282\"},{\"title\":\"Final Design of the Production SSR1 Cryomodule for PIP-II Project at   Fermilab\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2311.05475\"},{\"title\":\"Nuclear Engineering and Design 218 (2002) 25–32\",\"url\":\"https://www.gen-4.org/gif/upload/docs/application/pdf/2022-12/the-design-features-of-the-htr-10_2002_nuclear-engineering-and-design.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Benchmark Analysis Related to the PBMR-400, PBMM, GT ...\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/Publications/PDF/TE-1694_web.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Design of a Helium Passivation System for the Target Vessel of the Beam   Dump Facility at CERN\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/1910.00333\"},{\"title\":\"Core thermal–hydraulic design - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549304002365\"},{\"title\":\"Design and construction of a cryogenic subcooler-box for supplying single phase supercritical helium to dark matter and gravitational wave experiments\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.08496\"}]\n\nI found some relevant information about high-temperature reactors. Based on the search results, I can see references to the HTTR (High Temperature Test Reactor) and HTR-10, which are helium-cooled reactors with operating parameters that partially match your query.\n\nThe HTTR is a helium-cooled, graphite moderated high-temperature reactor with 30 MW thermal power and a reactor outlet coolant temperature of 950 °C.\n\nHowever, the specific parameters you mentioned (10.2 kg/s mass flow rate, 4 MPa coolant pressure, 395°C inlet temperature, and 850/950°C outlet temperatures) don't appear directly in these results. \n\nThe closest match I found is for the HTR-10: The HTR-10 has a primary helium pressure of 3.0 MPa, a helium mass flow rate at full power of 4.3 kg/s, and average helium temperatures of 250/700°C at reactor inlet/outlet.\n\nFor more specific information about HTTR design parameters with exactly 10.2 kg/s flow rate and 4 MPa pressure, you may need to consult detailed HTTR technical documentation or design reports directly, as these specific combined parameters don't appear in the current search results.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"58f3dca5-f961-43f5-a628-54a471156bbd","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:10:56.961Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
