{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CpgHrya49ZtTALJ1RE7BGC","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"HTTR graphite IG-110 reflector boron impurity content ppm delayed neutron fraction beta effective core physics\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Calculation of the effect of boron as impurity on the reactivity of the Miniature Neutron Source Reactors using the MCNP code - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0149197014003552\"},{\"title\":\"GTHTR300 design and development\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/222749567_GTHTR300_design_and_development\"},{\"title\":\"Japan Atomic Energy Agency 日本原子力研究開発機構機関リポジトリ\",\"url\":\"https://jopss.jaea.go.jp/pdfdata/AA2018-0707.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Determination of impurity distribution in IG-11/110 nuclear graphite using TOF-SIMS - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0022311523005810\"},{\"title\":\"Characteristics of first loaded IG-110 graphite in HTTR core\",\"url\":\"https://inis.iaea.org/search/search.aspx?orig_q=RN%3A38056758\"},{\"title\":\"This is a preprint of a paper intended for publication in a journal or\",\"url\":\"https://inldigitallibrary.inl.gov/sites/sti/sti/4247200.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"PHYSOR 2010 – Advances in Reactor Physics to Power the Nuclear Renaissance\",\"url\":\"https://www.ornl.gov/file/scale-6-analysis-htr-10-pebble-bed-reactor-initial-critical-configuration/display\"},{\"title\":\"Vapor deposition apparatus and techniques using high puritiy polymer derived silicon carbide\",\"url\":\"https://image-ppubs.uspto.gov/dirsearch-public/print/downloadPdf/10753010\"},{\"title\":\"Historic and modern nuclear graphite impurities: Pathways to improved waste strategies - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1359028625000294\"}]\n\nNow let me search for more specific information about delayed neutron fraction and effective core physics parameters:\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Effective Delayed Neutron Fraction – βeff - Beta Effective\",\"url\":\"https://www.nuclear-power.com/nuclear-power/fission/delayed-neutrons/effective-delayed-neutron-fraction-%CE%B2eff/\"},{\"title\":\"Measured and calculated effective delayed neutron fraction of the IPR-R1 Triga reactor\",\"url\":\"https://inis.iaea.org/records/hvcvw-yqk10\"},{\"title\":\"MEASURED AND CALCULATED EFFECTIVE DELAYED ...\",\"url\":\"https://www.osti.gov/etdeweb/servlets/purl/21511800\"},{\"title\":\"Analysis of benchmark experiments of effective delayed neutron fraction βeff at FCA - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0149197099000141\"},{\"title\":\"Study on the Characteristics of Effective Delayed Neutron Fraction (βeff) for Pebble-Bed Reactor with Plutonium Fuel | Iranian Journal of Science | Springer Nature Link\",\"url\":\"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s40995-019-00772-8\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) Effective delayed neutron fraction and prompt neutron lifetime of Tehran research reactor mixed-core\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/257159796_Effective_delayed_neutron_fraction_and_prompt_neutron_lifetime_of_Tehran_research_reactor_mixed-core\"},{\"title\":\"Calculating the Effective Delayed Neutron Fraction (β\",\"url\":\"https://www.ornl.gov/file/02alexshawornl/display\"},{\"title\":\"Effective Delayed Neutron Fraction | Springer Nature Link\",\"url\":\"https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-981-16-0344-0_4\"}]\n\nBased on my web search results, I found relevant information about HTTR IG-110 graphite, boron impurity content, and core physics. Here's what I found:\n\n## HTTR IG-110 Graphite and Boron Impurity Content\n\nHTTR employs high purify nuclear graphite named IG-110 from the viewpoint of criticality. GTHTR300, commercial-scale HTGR, employed fine purified grade graphite material IG-110 for the reflector blocks.\n\nRegarding boron impurity content, IG-110 nuclear grade graphite has an ash content of 12.7 ppm, and all graphites analyzed belong to the High Purity class (EBC < 2 ppm). This contrasts with IG-11, which has an equivalent boron content of 3 ppm and ash content of 500 ppm.\n\n## Impact on Core Physics\n\nThe boron content in reflector graphite has significant effects on core physics. A slight increase in the equivalent boron content of the core graphite can significantly decrease the effective eigenvalue: -0.013 ± 0.0003 keff/ppm and -0.0019 ± 0.0003 keff/ppm for impurities in the graphite blocks and permanent reflector, respectively.\n\nRegarding delayed neutron fraction, the effectively delayed neutron fraction usually referred to as βeff, is the same fraction at thermal energies, and the effectively delayed neutron fraction reflects the ability of the reactor to thermalize and utilize each neutron produced.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"d625c1a3-5709-4604-b6b1-63962cd70ca3","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:11:01.945Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
