{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RkHMN57riumba6dug3ufpk","type":"tool_result","content":"I apologize, but I cannot extract the HTTR fuel design specifications from the provided content. The document appears to be a PDF file rendered as raw binary/encoded data, which is not human-readable in this format.\n\nTo provide accurate HTTR (High Temperature Engineering Test Reactor) TRISO particle specifications including kernel diameter, coating layer thicknesses, fuel compact dimensions, enrichment data, and fuel rod parameters, I would need:\n\n1. A properly decoded text version of the document\n2. Clear, legible text content rather than binary PDF encoding\n\nIf you can provide the document in text format, I'll be happy to extract the specific technical specifications you've requested with exact numbers and units, maintaining the 125-character quote limit and proper attribution.\n\n[Binary content (application/pdf, 309.2KB) also saved to /root/.claude/projects/-root-bench-httr/bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e/tool-results/webfetch-1783030279460-nd8i2k.pdf]"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"5fd7eda2-d588-4fce-8203-d6123705609d","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:11:22.770Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CH6yEycqFZ6dneVQqqeSn6","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"JAERI-1332 \"Design of the High Temperature Engineering Test Reactor HTTR\" Saito 1994\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Design of high temperature Engineering Test Reactor (HTTR) (Technical Report) | ETDEWEB\",\"url\":\"https://www.osti.gov/etdeweb/biblio/109497\"},{\"title\":\"Reactor internals design - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549304002407\"},{\"title\":\"Performance test of HTTR - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549304002596\"},{\"title\":\"Development of high temperature gas-cooled reactor (HTGR) fuel in Japan\",\"url\":\"https://oaktrust.library.tamu.edu/server/api/core/bitstreams/ec8a21d7-ff8b-4737-a132-be12235a1762/content\"},{\"title\":\"Structural design of high temperature metallic components - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549304002560\"},{\"title\":\"Design of high temperature Engineering Test Reactor (HTTR)\",\"url\":\"https://inis.iaea.org/search/search.aspx?orig_q=RN%3A27002401\"},{\"title\":\"Current status of high temperature gas-cooled reactor development in Japan - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549324004382\"},{\"title\":\"Plan for first phase of safety demonstration tests of the High Temperature Engineering Test Reactor (HTTR) - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549303001080\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) Research and development on high burnup HTGR fuels in JAEA\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/339159277_Research_and_development_on_high_burnup_HTGR_fuels_in_JAEA\"}]\n\nI found the document you're looking for. Here's what I found:\n\nJAERI-1332 is a technical report authored by Saito, Shinzo; Tanaka, Toshiyuki; and Sudo, Yukio from the Japan Atomic Energy Research Institute's Oarai Research Establishment, published in September 1994.\n\nThe HTTR is a graphite-moderated and helium gas-cooled reactor with 30 MW in thermal output and outlet coolant temperature of 850°C for rated operation and 950°C for high temperature test operation. It is planned to conduct various irradiation tests for fuels and materials, safety demonstration tests and nuclear heat application tests.\n\nThe report summarizes evaluation of nuclear and thermal-hydraulic characteristics, design outline of major systems and components, and includes relating R and D results and safety evaluation.\n\nThe document is available through the OSTI (Office of Scientific and Technical Information) database at https://www.osti.gov/etdeweb/biblio/109497.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"32af39fb-d185-4a7b-8766-ada402639ce9","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:11:25.437Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F9Jm2M9e68oZBoff6j28mR","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"Nuclear design\" HTTR Nakagawa Fujimoto Nojiri enrichment zones 12 core average 5.9 wt% burnable poison B4C\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Kiyonobu Yamashita's research works | Japan Atomic Energy Agency and other places\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/scientific-contributions/Kiyonobu-Yamashita-2001688966\"},{\"title\":\"Nozomu Fujimoto's research works | Japan Atomic Energy Agency and other places\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/scientific-contributions/Nozomu-Fujimoto-82760147\"},{\"title\":\"Nuclear design - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549304002353\"},{\"title\":\"Faculty Profiles - FUJIMOTO NOZOMU\",\"url\":\"https://hyoka.ofc.kyushu-u.ac.jp/html/100020644_en.html\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) Particle-type Burnable Poisons for Thorium-based Fuel in HTGR\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/278049502_Particle-type_Burnable_Poisons_for_Thorium-based_Fuel_in_HTGR\"},{\"title\":\"Nuclear design - Kyushu University Pure Portal Site\",\"url\":\"https://kyushu-u.elsevierpure.com/en/publications/nuclear-design/\"},{\"title\":\"Burnable poison optimized on a long-life, annular HTGR core | Request PDF\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/359396105_Burnable_poison_optimized_on_a_long-life_annular_HTGR_core\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found relevant information about the HTTR nuclear design. Here are the key findings:\n\n## Key Results:\n\nThe HTTR has been designed for an outlet temperature of 950°C, which is the highest temperature in the world for a block-type high-temperature gas-cooled reactor (HTGR).\n\n**Uranium Enrichment:** The core achieves optimal power distribution by changing uranium enrichment (3-10 wt.%U), with an average enrichment of 5.9 wt%.\n\n**Burnable Poison Design:** The HTTR is the first block-type HTGR designed for 950°C outlet gas temperature which uses low-enriched uranium fuel with burnable poison rod. The problem with excess reactivity was solved by optimizing burnable poisons (BPs) in the core, keeping the excess reactivity to the minimum necessary for reactor operations.\n\n**Design Authors:** The search results confirm that Nozomu Fujimoto, Naoki Nojiri, Hiroei Ando, and Kiyonobu Yamashita were involved in the nuclear design work.\n\nThe results indicate that the power distribution in the core was optimized by changing the uranium enrichment to maintain the fuel temperature at less than the limit (1600°C).\n\nHowever, the search results do not specifically mention \"12 core\" or detail about B4C burnable poison composition in the available excerpts.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"ca61aa18-78e1-4239-82c9-62ff86d3bff7","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:11:26.217Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
