{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RZK4T2VUKVD4AjeUM5JArW","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"HTTR core 30 fuel columns 5 blocks per column effective core diameter 2.3 m height 2.9 m control rod guide columns reflector\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Long-term high-temperature operation of the HTTR - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549311009241\"},{\"title\":\"CHARACTERISTICS OF HTTR's STARTUP PHYSICS TESTS XA9846691\",\"url\":\"https://www.osti.gov/etdeweb/servlets/purl/618628\"},{\"title\":\"Reactor core design of Gas Turbine High Temperature Reactor 300 - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549303004059\"},{\"title\":\"HTTR - PHYSOR2010\",\"url\":\"https://www.slideshare.net/jdbess/httr-physor2010\"},{\"title\":\"Deterministic Modeling of the High Temperature Test Reactor\",\"url\":\"https://inldigitallibrary.inl.gov/sites/sti/sti/4633194.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"High Temperature Engineering Test Reactor HTTR Description | VTB\",\"url\":\"https://mooseframework.inl.gov/virtual_test_bed/htgr/httr/httr_reactor_description.html\"},{\"title\":\"IAEA-TECDOC-1382 Evaluation of high temperature gas cooled reactor performance:\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/publications/PDF/te_1382_web/TE_1382_Part1.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Figure 5. HTTR fuel kernel to fuel column schematic.\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/HTTR-fuel-kernel-to-fuel-column-schematic_fig4_255217953\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) HTTR 30MWth Reactor with Homogenous (Th,U)O 2 Fuel\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/332915970_HTTR_30MWth_Reactor_with_Homogenous_ThUO_2_Fuel\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found detailed information about the HTTR core specifications you're asking about:\n\nThe active core of the HTTR consists of 30 fuel columns and 7 CR guide columns. Each fuel column stacks 5 fuel blocks and 4 reflector blocks. The size of the core is 2.9 m in height and 2.3 m in diameter.\n\nAdditional context: 9 more CR columns are distributed among the adjacent reflector graphite columns. The core follows vertical columns of hexagonal blocks arranged on a uniform triangular pitch. The triangular pitch of the columns on each support block is 36.2 cm at cold conditions.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"5f6a2654-de05-44c7-a8db-658ff528ffd8","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:12:20.467Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GWHVszYTduFtYD2cYGKnq7","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"HTTR helium primary flow rate 12.4 kg/s inlet 395 outlet 850 pressure 4 MPa rated operation JAERI\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"PNNL-20869 Prepared for the U.S. Nuclear Regulatory Commission\",\"url\":\"https://www.pnnl.gov/main/publications/external/technical_reports/pnnl-20869.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"High-temperature engineering test reactor — Grokipedia\",\"url\":\"https://grokipedia.com/page/high_temperature_engineering_test_reactor\"},{\"title\":\"REACTOR TECHNOLOGY DEVELOPMENT UNDER THE HTTR PROJECT Takakazu TAKIZUKA\",\"url\":\"https://www.ne.titech.ac.jp/archive/coe21/eng/events/ines1/pdf/87_takizuka.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Core thermal–hydraulic design - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549304002365\"},{\"title\":\"Present status of the HTTR project at JAERI - INIS-IAEA\",\"url\":\"https://inis.iaea.org/records/vrxcy-r3k32\"},{\"title\":\"Frontiers | Developing PCC and DCC integral effects test experiments at the High Temperature Test Facility\",\"url\":\"https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/energy-research/articles/10.3389/fenrg.2023.1088070/full\"},{\"title\":\"IAEA-TECDOC-1382 Evaluation of high temperature gas cooled reactor performance:\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/publications/PDF/te_1382_web/TE_1382_Part1.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"High efficiency Brayton cycles using LNG\",\"url\":\"https://image-ppubs.uspto.gov/dirsearch-public/print/downloadPdf/7028481\"},{\"title\":\"OECD PROCEEDINGS The first information exchange meeting on\",\"url\":\"https://www.oecd-nea.org/upload/docs/application/pdf/2019-12/hightemp.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Final Design Of The Pre-production SSR2 Cryomodule For PIP-II Project At   Fermilab\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2209.01282\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found information about the HTTR (High-Temperature Engineering Test Reactor) operated by JAERI that matches your specifications:\n\nApproximately 97% of the reactor thermal power is removed by the main cooling system with a helium flow of 12.4 kg/s at rated operation and 10.2 kg/s at the high-temperature test operation.\n\nThe primary system operates at 4 MPa pressure, with a primary inlet temperature of 395°C and primary outlet temperature of 850-950°C.\n\nThe HTTR is a graphite-moderated, helium-cooled research reactor located at the Oarai Research and Development Center in Ōarai, Ibaraki Prefecture, Japan, and operated by the Japan Atomic Energy Agency (JAEA).\n\nThe parameters you specified (12.4 kg/s helium flow rate at rated operation, inlet temperature of 395°C, outlet temperature of 850°C, and pressure of 4 MPa) are consistent with the HTTR's rated operational specifications documented in the technical literature.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"b65b0f01-bacd-4aa3-8889-a6f6475b6b96","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:12:22.019Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FucYXParwm1BVfVvGAQzUu","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"HTTR fuel compact packing fraction volume percent coated particles per compact burnable poison B4C H-451 graphite column\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Estimation of maximum coated particle fuel compact packing fraction - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0022311506005472\"},{\"title\":\"FABRICATION OF HTTR FIRST LOADING FUEL XA0100873\",\"url\":\"https://www.osti.gov/etdeweb/servlets/purl/20158164\"},{\"title\":\"Full article: Development plan of high burnup fuel for high temperature gas-cooled reactors in future\",\"url\":\"https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/00223131.2014.924886\"},{\"title\":\"Comparative modeling of stochastic versus regular arrangement of TRISO particles in HTTR - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0149197014002625\"},{\"title\":\"Neutronic characteristic of HTTR fuel compact with various packing models of coated fuel particle\",\"url\":\"https://inis.iaea.org/records/he9vs-ygz07\"},{\"title\":\"IAEA TECDOC SERIES Coated Particle Fuels for High Temperature Gas Cooled\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/publications/PDF/TE-2090web.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Fuel compact\",\"url\":\"https://image-ppubs.uspto.gov/dirsearch-public/print/downloadPdf/8599993\"}]\n\nLet me search for more specific information about HTTR fuel compact specifications including burnable poison and volume percentages.\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Decay Heat Quantification in the High-Temperature Test Reactor\",\"url\":\"https://inldigitallibrary.inl.gov/sites/sti/sti/Sort_1844.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Validation of McCARD for VHTR core with HTTR Benchmark\",\"url\":\"https://www.kns.org/files/int_paper/paper/MC2017_2017_2/P148S02-07ParkJS.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) HTTR 30MWth Reactor with Homogenous (Th,U)O 2 Fuel\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/332915970_HTTR_30MWth_Reactor_with_Homogenous_ThUO_2_Fuel\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) Particle-type Burnable Poisons for Thorium-based Fuel in HTGR\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/278049502_Particle-type_Burnable_Poisons_for_Thorium-based_Fuel_in_HTGR\"},{\"title\":\"IAEA-TECDOC-1382 Evaluation of high temperature gas cooled reactor performance:\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/publications/PDF/te_1382_web/TE_1382_Part1.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Optimization of Burnable Poison Loading for HTGR Cores with OTTO Refueling - ADS\",\"url\":\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2008NSE...158..264T/abstract\"},{\"title\":\"Optimization of Burnable Poison Loading for HTGR Cores with OTTO Refueling: Nuclear Science and Engineering: Vol 158, No 3\",\"url\":\"https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.13182/NSE08-A2752\"},{\"title\":\"High Temperature Engineering Test Reactor HTTR Description | VTB\",\"url\":\"https://mooseframework.inl.gov/virtual_test_bed/htgr/httr/httr_reactor_description.html\"},{\"title\":\"Moderator rod containing burnable poison and fuel assembly utilizing same\",\"url\":\"https://image-ppubs.uspto.gov/dirsearch-public/print/downloadPdf/5416813\"}]\n\nLet me search for more specific information about H-451 graphite specifications for HTTR fuel compacts.\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Long term reactivity operation for a high temperature testing reactor (HTTR) loaded with uranium nitride fuel - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0149197024002622\"},{\"title\":\"HTTR fuel kernel to fuel column schematic. | Download Scientific Diagram\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/HTTR-fuel-kernel-to-fuel-column-schematic_fig4_255217953\"},{\"title\":\"FABRICATION OF HTTR FIRST LOADING FUEL XA0100873\",\"url\":\"https://www.osti.gov/etdeweb/servlets/purl/20158164\"},{\"title\":\"Full article: Fuel performance under continuous high-temperature operation of the HTTR\",\"url\":\"https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/00223131.2014.926230\"},{\"title\":\"Major specification of HTTR | Download Table\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/Major-specification-of-HTTR_tbl1_261661742\"},{\"title\":\"IAEA TECDOC SERIES Coated Particle Fuels for High Temperature Gas Cooled\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/publications/PDF/TE-2090web.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Assessment of grade H-451 graphite for replaceable fuel and reflector elements in HTGR - UNT Digital Library\",\"url\":\"https://digital.library.unt.edu/ark:/67531/metadc1060758/\"},{\"title\":\"Fuel compact\",\"url\":\"https://image-ppubs.uspto.gov/dirsearch-public/print/downloadPdf/8599993\"}]\n\nBased on my search results, I found the following information relevant to your query about HTTR fuel compacts:\n\n## Key HTTR Fuel Compact Specifications:\n\n**Coated Particles per Compact:**\nEach fuel compact contains 13,000 TRISO particles with a diameter of 0.92 mm.\n\n**Packing Fraction:**\nA conservative estimate of the packing fraction limit is 0.44 for an HTGR compact within a graphite matrix, although packing fractions of up to 0.50 have been reported experimentally.\n\n**Burnable Poison (B4C) Specifications:**\nThere are two burnable poison (BP) channels containing B4C with 2.0 wt.% 10B enrichment. Additionally, the burnable poison rod is composed of 20 B4C pellets (40cm) and 20 graphite disks (10cm), with two types of burnable poison rod: H-1 type uses 2.22 wt.% and H-2 type uses 2.74 wt.% enrichment of 10B.\n\n**TRISO Particle Details:**\nFor HTTR TRISO fuel types, coating layers are composed of 60 µm of low-density buffer, 30 µm of high-density PyC, 25 µm of SiC and 45 µm of high-density PyC with a fuel kernel radius of 300 µm.\n\n**Graphite Matrix:**\nThe density of graphite matrix outside the fuel particles in the fuel compact region is 1.7 g/cm³.\n\n**Fuel Rod and Column Structure:**\nThe fuel block contains 31 or 33 fuel rods, and each fuel rod contains 14 fuel compacts.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"8b5db4ff-165e-4c75-9fea-75659ce14c89","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:12:31.452Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
