ach section contains five sintered compacts of B4C and C as neutron absorbers in the\n950:\fcenter to the outside, as shown in Figure 14. Both R2 and R3 CRs are in the replaceable reflector region\n968:absorb the impact of a CR. The annular space of each absorber section contains the sintered compacts\n969:with a density of 1.9 g/cm3.\n973:The RSS absorbers are a system of pellets produced by sintering B4C powder and graphite. These\n974:pellets can be released from the storage hoppers into holes in the CR guide columns to act as a backup\n979:block of the CR guide column contains B4C/C pins for thermal neutron shield. Specifications for CR\n1003:Density (g/cm3)\n1010:Sintered Compact of B4C/C\n1011:Natural Boron Concentration (wt%)\n1020:Drop B4C/C Pellets by Gravity\n1026:Packing Fraction (vol%)\n1028:B4C/C Graphite Pellets\n1029:Density (g/cm3)\n1036:Sintered Compact of B4C/C\n1037:Natural Boron Concentration (wt%)\n1050:\fTable 6. Specifications of reflector blocks and CR guide blocks.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"677c5591-fcdd-41ad-9796-df6230c3562b","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:13:25.394Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
