{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UGeDCtf2oA2FoSqXUaGksV","type":"tool_result","content":"# HTTR Startup Physics Test Parameters\n\nBased on the PDF content provided (which appears to be heavily encoded/compressed JBIG2 image data rather than readable text), I cannot reliably extract the specific steady-state design/physics parameters you requested.\n\nTo accurately provide:\n- Effective delayed neutron fraction (β_eff)\n- Prompt neutron lifetime/generation time\n- Excess reactivity\n- Number of fuel columns for criticality\n- Temperature coefficient of reactivity (isothermal)\n- Core-average enrichment\n\n**I would need access to the actual readable text content of the HTTR startup physics test document.** The material provided consists primarily of compressed image streams and PDF structural data that cannot be meaningfully parsed for numerical physics parameters.\n\nIf you have access to the document in a text-readable format (plain text, OCR-processed PDF, or HTML), please share that instead, and I can extract these specific parameters with precision.\n\n[Binary content (application/pdf, 309.3KB) also saved to /root/.claude/projects/-root-bench-httr/bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e/tool-results/webfetch-1783030433887-0j7z5q.pdf]"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"27fec9c8-6c5e-4c92-941b-c51e279b6b72","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:13:57.419Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DXWkwQhsvyJQZDxWChbaPg","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"HTTR vessel cooling system VCS heat removal capacity MW passive residual heat removal reactor pressure vessel\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Passive heat removal by vessel cooling system of HTTR during no forced cooling accidents - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/002954939601268X\"},{\"title\":\"Evaluation of a Vessel Cooling System for the VHTR | Request PDF\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/267576165_Evaluation_of_a_Vessel_Cooling_System_for_the_VHTR\"},{\"title\":\"Design and fabrication of the reactor Vessel Cooling System (VCS) in HTTR\",\"url\":\"https://inis.iaea.org/records/h75a9-kty70\"},{\"title\":\"Development of a new decay heat removal system for a high temperature gas-cooled reactor - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0306454907000886\"},{\"title\":\"IAEA-TECDOC-1382 Evaluation of high temperature gas cooled reactor performance:\",\"url\":\"https://catatanstudi.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/2003-evaluation-of-htgr-performance-benchmark-analysis-related-to-initial-testing-of-the-httr-and-htr-10_iaea.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Passive residual heat removal system and nuclear power plant equipment\",\"url\":\"https://image-ppubs.uspto.gov/dirsearch-public/print/downloadPdf/9312034\"},{\"title\":\"Reliability and availability simulation for vessel cooling system of the high temperature engineering test reactor - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0149197023003232\"},{\"title\":\"Liquid metal reactor air cooling baffle\",\"url\":\"https://image-ppubs.uspto.gov/dirsearch-public/print/downloadPdf/5339340\"},{\"title\":\"Full pressure passive emergency core cooling and residual heat removal system for water cooled nuclear reactors\",\"url\":\"https://image-ppubs.uspto.gov/dirsearch-public/print/downloadPdf/5102616\"},{\"title\":\"New reactor cavity cooling system having passive safety features using novel shape for HTGRs and VHTRs - Advances in Engineering\",\"url\":\"https://advanceseng.com/new-reactor-cavity-cooling-system-having-passive-safety-features-using-novel-shape-for-htgrs-and-vhtrs/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found regarding the HTTR vessel cooling system:\n\n## Overview of the VCS\n\nThe HTTR has two independent vessel cooling systems (VCSs) that cool the reactor core indirectly during depressurized and pressurized accidents, with each VCS consisting of a water cooling loop and cooling panels around the reactor pressure vessel (RPV).\n\nThe reactor Vessel Cooling System (VCS) is one of the engineered safety features used as a residual heat removal system when forced circulation in both the primary and auxiliary cooling systems cannot be performed simultaneously.\n\n## Heat Removal Capacity\n\nThe search results indicate that the RCCS can passively remove 800 kW in the HTTR, which is equivalent to 2.67% of the decay heat of the rated operation of 30 MW at the elapsed time of 40-100 seconds after reactor shutdown.\n\n## System Design and Function\n\nThe VCS consists of the upper, lower, and side cooling panels situated around the Reactor Pressure Vessel (RPV) and supplied with water from two independent lines, and in case of Loss of Forced Cooling (LOFC), the VCS is to remove the residual heat from both the core and RPV.\n\nThe cooling panels, kept below 90°C, cool the RPV by radiation and natural convection and remove the decay heat from the reactor core during these accidents.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"a2c79dad-0e1e-4384-be04-e99a91428fb4","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:13:58.103Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
