{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kjhvrp2AZbcdSjcADfVR41","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"HTTR effective delayed neutron fraction beta_eff prompt neutron generation lifetime value pcm reactor kinetics\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Calculation of the effective delayed-neutron fraction and prompt-neutron lifetime in IBR-2M | Atomic Energy\",\"url\":\"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10512-011-9463-8\"},{\"title\":\"Prompt Neutron Lifetime - an overview | ScienceDirect Topics\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/engineering/prompt-neutron-lifetime\"},{\"title\":\"Effective delayed neutron fraction and prompt neutron lifetime of Tehran research reactor - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0306454903000811\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) Effective delayed neutron fraction and prompt neutron lifetime of Tehran research reactor mixed-core\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/257159796_Effective_delayed_neutron_fraction_and_prompt_neutron_lifetime_of_Tehran_research_reactor_mixed-core\"},{\"title\":\"BETALS: a Fortran II program for calculating beta-effective ($beta$/sub eff/) and prompt neutron lifetime (l/sub p/) for a reactor with given flux (phi) and adjoint (phi$sup +$) solutions (Technical Report) | OSTI.GOV\",\"url\":\"https://www.osti.gov/biblio/4256797-betals-fortran-ii-program-calculating-beta-effective-beta-sub-eff-prompt-neutron-lifetime-sub-reactor-given-flux-phi-adjoint-phi-sup-solutions\"},{\"title\":\"Rossi-alpha Benchmark Validation of a Static Alpha Eigenvalue Capability in OpenMC\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2606.00907\"},{\"title\":\"Effective delayed neutron fraction and prompt neutron lifetime of Tehran research reactor mixed-core - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0306454912004781\"}]\n\nI found some general information about effective delayed neutron fraction (β_eff) and prompt neutron lifetime in reactor kinetics. However, the search results don't contain specific data for the HTTR (High Temperature Test Reactor). Let me search more specifically for HTTR kinetics parameters.\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Evaluation of the HTTR criticality and burnup calculations with continuous-energy and multigroup cross sections - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0029549313006419\"},{\"title\":\"Outline of High Temperature Engineering Test Reactor\",\"url\":\"https://www.jaea.go.jp/04/o-arai/nhc/en/faq/httr.html\"},{\"title\":\"Full article: Experiments and validation analyses of HTTR on loss of forced cooling under 30% reactor power\",\"url\":\"https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/00223131.2014.967324\"},{\"title\":\"High Temperature Engineering Test Reactor HTTR Steady State Multiphysics Model Description | vtb\",\"url\":\"https://mooseframework.inl.gov/virtual_test_bed/htgr/httr/httr_steady_state_model_description.html\"},{\"title\":\"High Temperature Engineering Test Reactor HTTR Description | VTB\",\"url\":\"https://mooseframework.inl.gov/virtual_test_bed/htgr/httr/httr_reactor_description.html\"},{\"title\":\"IAEA-TECDOC-1382 Evaluation of high temperature gas cooled reactor performance:\",\"url\":\"https://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/publications/PDF/te_1382_web/TE_1382_Part1.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"RELAP5-3D Capabilities for High Temperature Gas\",\"url\":\"https://www.osti.gov/servlets/purl/3013713\"}]\n\nLet me search more specifically for HTTR reactor kinetics parameters including beta_eff values.\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Prompt Neutron Lifetime - an overview | ScienceDirect Topics\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/engineering/prompt-neutron-lifetime\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) Effective delayed neutron fraction and prompt neutron lifetime of Tehran research reactor mixed-core\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/257159796_Effective_delayed_neutron_fraction_and_prompt_neutron_lifetime_of_Tehran_research_reactor_mixed-core\"},{\"title\":\"Effective delayed neutron fraction and prompt neutron lifetime of Tehran research reactor mixed-core - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0306454912004781\"},{\"title\":\"KINETIC PARAMETERS CALCULATION DURING FIRST CYCLE OF THE WWER-1000 REACTOR CORE\",\"url\":\"https://pubs.cnl.ca/doi/full/10.12943/CNR.2017.00017\"},{\"title\":\"Mean Generation Time with Delayed Neutrons\",\"url\":\"https://www.nuclear-power.com/nuclear-power/fission/delayed-neutrons/mean-generation-time-with-delayed-neutrons/\"},{\"title\":\"PADINE-TT Project - Procedure for the experiment at Training Reactor VR-1 1\",\"url\":\"https://ec.europa.eu/programmes/erasmus-plus/project-result-content/fbcfee8c-7b46-4e39-a5eb-129ea94d51c7/CTU1_Delayed_neutrons_part_2_Experiment_procedure_for_students.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"331-1 P.62 CHE 3804 NUCLEAR ENGINEERING SECTIONS REACTOR KINETICS\",\"url\":\"https://canteach.candu.org/Content%20Library/20041708.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Prompt Neutron - an overview | ScienceDirect Topics\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/engineering/prompt-neutron\"},{\"title\":\"Inhour equation - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inhour_equation\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results, I have found general information about reactor kinetics parameters, but I haven't located specific published values for the HTTR's beta_eff and prompt neutron generation lifetime yet. Let me try one more targeted search.\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Effective Delayed Neutron Fraction – βeff - Beta Effective\",\"url\":\"https://www.nuclear-power.com/nuclear-power/fission/delayed-neutrons/effective-delayed-neutron-fraction-%CE%B2eff/\"},{\"title\":\"Effective delayed neutron fraction and prompt neutron lifetime of Tehran research reactor - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0306454903000811\"},{\"title\":\"Prompt Neutron - an overview | ScienceDirect Topics\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/engineering/prompt-neutron\"},{\"title\":\"Review and comparison of effective delayed neutron fraction calculation methods with Monte Carlo codes - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S030645491300635X\"},{\"title\":\"Prompt Neutron Lifetime - an overview | ScienceDirect Topics\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/engineering/prompt-neutron-lifetime\"},{\"title\":\"Calculation of the Effective Delayed Neutron Fraction by Deterministic and Monte Carlo Methods - Carta - 2011 - Science and Technology of Nuclear Installations - Wiley Online Library\",\"url\":\"https://www.hindawi.com/journals/stni/2011/584256/\"},{\"title\":\"Development of a Reference Database for Beta-Delayed Neutron Emission\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2102.01165\"},{\"title\":\"Measurements of effective delayed neutron fraction in a fast neutron   reactor using the perturbation method\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/1510.06276\"},{\"title\":\"Effective of prompt and delayed gamma emission on the nuclear radiation shielding effectiveness of prevalent natural minerals\",\"url\":\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC12603030/\"}]\n\nBased on my web searches, I was unable to find specific published values for the HTTR (High Temperature Engineering Test Reactor) reactor's effective delayed neutron fraction (β_eff) and prompt neutron generation lifetime in the search results.\n\nHowever, I can provide you with general context about these reactor kinetics parameters:\n\n**General Information Found:**\n\nThe effective delayed neutron fraction, βeff, needs to be defined, particularly in thermal reactors (~0.0065 for uranium-235 fuel). \n\nFor reactors like CANDU and graphite moderated-gas cooled reactors, prompt neutron lifetime is in the range of ~10−3 s. Since the HTTR is a graphite-moderated, helium-cooled reactor, its prompt neutron lifetime would likely fall in this range.\n\nEffective delayed neutron fraction βeff and neutron generation time Λ are important factors in reactor physics calculation and transient analysis.\n\n**Regarding the HTTR specifically:** The search results contained general information about HTTR's design and operation, but did not include the specific kinetic parameters you requested. To find these specific values, you may need to consult:\n\n1. JAEA (Japan Atomic Energy Agency) technical reports on HTTR\n2. IAEA-TECDOC publications on high-temperature gas-cooled reactors\n3. Peer-reviewed publications specifically focused on HTTR neutronics analysis or safety analysis reports\n\nWould you like me to search for these specific documents, or do you have access to HTTR safety analysis reports that might contain these parameters?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nSoKQZw2ozs6fpCh9kUjQ","session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"5be2f1ac-b963-4e2b-97d7-7f50f70cfe14","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:14:03.467Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Collect HTTR design data"}
