{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01BdfGA4kUcFybzE1MZKCCtF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014cDjhYwukdRLthwSKnDGcx","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/root/bench/httr/output/PROGRESS.md","old_string":"- 22:08 OpenMC installed & verified. XS download launched (pid in /root/xs/dl.log).","new_string":"- 22:08 OpenMC installed & verified. XS download launched.\n- 22:11 ENDF/B-VIII.0 downloaded (3.4 GB) + extracted to /root/xs/endfb-viii.0-hdf5/. Confirmed T=294/600/900/1200/2500 K and c_Graphite / c_Graphite_30p / c_U_in_UO2 / c_O_in_UO2 S(a,b). Steps 1-2 DONE.\n- 22:12 Design-data research agent running. Next: build TRISO pin-cell model.\n- Modeling decision: compute k_inf(T) of the HTTR average fuel lattice (pin-in-block cell, explicit TRISO double heterogeneity, reflective BC) at 294/600/900/1200 K -> isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T). Absolute criticality is set by frozen control rods in reality, so the transient needs the SHAPE alpha(T), which the reflected lattice captures robustly. Will note leakage/reflector caveat.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1017,"cache_read_input_tokens":53427,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1017},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"57ce4ea5-a608-4217-9350-382d57a16367","request_id":"req_011CcdzywFbeyE9rJk7s5a9B"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014cDjhYwukdRLthwSKnDGcx","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /root/bench/httr/output/PROGRESS.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"b903909c-7a52-4298-8f5a-1f12a51af3c9","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:15:41.199Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/root/bench/httr/output/PROGRESS.md","oldString":"- 22:08 OpenMC installed & verified. XS download launched (pid in /root/xs/dl.log).","newString":"- 22:08 OpenMC installed & verified. XS download launched.\n- 22:11 ENDF/B-VIII.0 downloaded (3.4 GB) + extracted to /root/xs/endfb-viii.0-hdf5/. Confirmed T=294/600/900/1200/2500 K and c_Graphite / c_Graphite_30p / c_U_in_UO2 / c_O_in_UO2 S(a,b). Steps 1-2 DONE.\n- 22:12 Design-data research agent running. Next: build TRISO pin-cell model.\n- Modeling decision: compute k_inf(T) of the HTTR average fuel lattice (pin-in-block cell, explicit TRISO double heterogeneity, reflective BC) at 294/600/900/1200 K -> isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T). Absolute criticality is set by frozen control rods in reality, so the transient needs the SHAPE alpha(T), which the reflected lattice captures robustly. Will note leakage/reflector caveat.\n","originalFile":"# PROGRESS — HTTR LOFC prediction\n\nStarted: 2026-07-02 22:08 UTC\n\n## Plan\n1. [DONE] Install OpenMC (0.15.3, conda-forge, MPI) in env `omc`.\n2. [RUNNING] Download ENDF/B-VIII.0 HDF5 nuclear data (~2.5 GB) -> /root/xs/. Has T=250/293.6/600/900/1200/2500 K + graphite S(a,b). ETA ~few min.\n3. [ ] Collect HTTR public DESIGN data (geometry, enrichment zoning, materials, thermal props). Log in sources.md.\n4. [ ] Build OpenMC model: TRISO compact -> fuel rod -> hex fuel block -> full core (reflected) with enrichment zoning.\n5. [ ] Compute k_eff at isothermal T = 300, 600, 900, 1200 K (whole core = fuel+graphite+He same T). Long MC, low sigma.\n6. [ ] Derive isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T) [pcm/K] with statistical uncertainties.\n7. [ ] Build coupled transient model: point kinetics + ANS decay heat + lumped thermal (fuel/graphite/vessel) + VCS heat sink.\n8. [ ] Run LOFC transient: circulator trip at 9 MWt, no scram, rods frozen, VCS on.\n9. [ ] Extract 4 predictions + confidence levels. Write calculation_note.md.\n\n## Status log\n- 22:08 OpenMC installed & verified. XS download launched (pid in /root/xs/dl.log).\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":14,"oldLines":4,"newStart":14,"newLines":8,"lines":[" 9. [ ] Extract 4 predictions + confidence levels. Write calculation_note.md."," "," ## Status log","-- 22:08 OpenMC installed & verified. XS download launched (pid in /root/xs/dl.log).","+- 22:08 OpenMC installed & verified. XS download launched.","+- 22:11 ENDF/B-VIII.0 downloaded (3.4 GB) + extracted to /root/xs/endfb-viii.0-hdf5/. Confirmed T=294/600/900/1200/2500 K and c_Graphite / c_Graphite_30p / c_U_in_UO2 / c_O_in_UO2 S(a,b). Steps 1-2 DONE.","+- 22:12 Design-data research agent running. Next: build TRISO pin-cell model.","+- Modeling decision: compute k_inf(T) of the HTTR average fuel lattice (pin-in-block cell, explicit TRISO double heterogeneity, reflective BC) at 294/600/900/1200 K -> isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T). Absolute criticality is set by frozen control rods in reality, so the transient needs the SHAPE alpha(T), which the reflected lattice captures robustly. Will note leakage/reflector caveat.","+"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
