{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01JQtL1LNqamamH7okKAnBLa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NAzoErH4vdoiJat5TCCxNQ","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/root/bench/httr/output/PROGRESS.md","old_string":"- Modeling decision: compute k_inf(T) of the HTTR average fuel lattice (pin-in-block cell, explicit TRISO double heterogeneity, reflective BC) at 294/600/900/1200 K -> isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T). Absolute criticality is set by frozen control rods in reality, so the transient needs the SHAPE alpha(T), which the reflected lattice captures robustly. Will note leakage/reflector caveat.","new_string":"- Modeling decision: compute k_inf(T) of the HTTR average fuel lattice (pin-in-block cell, explicit TRISO double heterogeneity, reflective BC) at 294/600/900/1200 K -> isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T). Absolute criticality is set by frozen control rods in reality, so the transient needs the SHAPE alpha(T), which the reflected lattice captures robustly. Will note leakage/reflector caveat.\n- 22:2x Design data agent returned full report (geometry/enrichment/BP/graphite/VCS/kinetics), sources.md populated, LOFC incident logged.\n- Built model_httr.py (TRISO pin-in-block WS cell, smeared burnable poison, --prompt-only for beta_eff) and transient.py (point kinetics + ANS decay heat + 2-node graphite thermal + VCS). Pipeline validated on synthetic k(T): power collapses in ~6-18 min, core overshoots then cools, recriticality when core returns to Top, self-regulates at low power, temps bounded.\n- Geometry cross-check: HM ~930 kg (matches HTTR ~900 kg U), active-core graphite 13.7 t, reflector ~90 t (~0.9 m responds over 24 h). Responsive graphite thermal mass ~50-70 t.\n- [RUNNING] OpenMC main sweep (BP on, 12000 p x 170 batches) T=294/600/900/1200 K. First temp computing (~20 min/temp). Then: beta_eff (prompt-only @900K), no-BP sensitivity, then transient + sensitivity study."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2371,"cache_read_input_tokens":127742,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2371},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"4f8ea24c-f99e-4395-81e2-5712804393c5","request_id":"req_011Cce2MkpmPMEx7FkXZwT5N"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NAzoErH4vdoiJat5TCCxNQ","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /root/bench/httr/output/PROGRESS.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"a6eff388-98f3-46f0-9cba-ebf70d87b1d8","timestamp":"2026-07-02T22:32:20.345Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/root/bench/httr/output/PROGRESS.md","oldString":"- Modeling decision: compute k_inf(T) of the HTTR average fuel lattice (pin-in-block cell, explicit TRISO double heterogeneity, reflective BC) at 294/600/900/1200 K -> isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T). Absolute criticality is set by frozen control rods in reality, so the transient needs the SHAPE alpha(T), which the reflected lattice captures robustly. Will note leakage/reflector caveat.","newString":"- Modeling decision: compute k_inf(T) of the HTTR average fuel lattice (pin-in-block cell, explicit TRISO double heterogeneity, reflective BC) at 294/600/900/1200 K -> isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T). Absolute criticality is set by frozen control rods in reality, so the transient needs the SHAPE alpha(T), which the reflected lattice captures robustly. Will note leakage/reflector caveat.\n- 22:2x Design data agent returned full report (geometry/enrichment/BP/graphite/VCS/kinetics), sources.md populated, LOFC incident logged.\n- Built model_httr.py (TRISO pin-in-block WS cell, smeared burnable poison, --prompt-only for beta_eff) and transient.py (point kinetics + ANS decay heat + 2-node graphite thermal + VCS). Pipeline validated on synthetic k(T): power collapses in ~6-18 min, core overshoots then cools, recriticality when core returns to Top, self-regulates at low power, temps bounded.\n- Geometry cross-check: HM ~930 kg (matches HTTR ~900 kg U), active-core graphite 13.7 t, reflector ~90 t (~0.9 m responds over 24 h). Responsive graphite thermal mass ~50-70 t.\n- [RUNNING] OpenMC main sweep (BP on, 12000 p x 170 batches) T=294/600/900/1200 K. First temp computing (~20 min/temp). Then: beta_eff (prompt-only @900K), no-BP sensitivity, then transient + sensitivity study.","originalFile":"# PROGRESS — HTTR LOFC prediction\n\nStarted: 2026-07-02 22:08 UTC\n\n## Plan\n1. [DONE] Install OpenMC (0.15.3, conda-forge, MPI) in env `omc`.\n2. [RUNNING] Download ENDF/B-VIII.0 HDF5 nuclear data (~2.5 GB) -> /root/xs/. Has T=250/293.6/600/900/1200/2500 K + graphite S(a,b). ETA ~few min.\n3. [ ] Collect HTTR public DESIGN data (geometry, enrichment zoning, materials, thermal props). Log in sources.md.\n4. [ ] Build OpenMC model: TRISO compact -> fuel rod -> hex fuel block -> full core (reflected) with enrichment zoning.\n5. [ ] Compute k_eff at isothermal T = 300, 600, 900, 1200 K (whole core = fuel+graphite+He same T). Long MC, low sigma.\n6. [ ] Derive isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T) [pcm/K] with statistical uncertainties.\n7. [ ] Build coupled transient model: point kinetics + ANS decay heat + lumped thermal (fuel/graphite/vessel) + VCS heat sink.\n8. [ ] Run LOFC transient: circulator trip at 9 MWt, no scram, rods frozen, VCS on.\n9. [ ] Extract 4 predictions + confidence levels. Write calculation_note.md.\n\n## Status log\n- 22:08 OpenMC installed & verified. XS download launched.\n- 22:11 ENDF/B-VIII.0 downloaded (3.4 GB) + extracted to /root/xs/endfb-viii.0-hdf5/. Confirmed T=294/600/900/1200/2500 K and c_Graphite / c_Graphite_30p / c_U_in_UO2 / c_O_in_UO2 S(a,b). Steps 1-2 DONE.\n- 22:12 Design-data research agent running. Next: build TRISO pin-cell model.\n- Modeling decision: compute k_inf(T) of the HTTR average fuel lattice (pin-in-block cell, explicit TRISO double heterogeneity, reflective BC) at 294/600/900/1200 K -> isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T). Absolute criticality is set by frozen control rods in reality, so the transient needs the SHAPE alpha(T), which the reflected lattice captures robustly. Will note leakage/reflector caveat.\n\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":18,"oldLines":4,"newStart":18,"newLines":8,"lines":[" - 22:11 ENDF/B-VIII.0 downloaded (3.4 GB) + extracted to /root/xs/endfb-viii.0-hdf5/. Confirmed T=294/600/900/1200/2500 K and c_Graphite / c_Graphite_30p / c_U_in_UO2 / c_O_in_UO2 S(a,b). Steps 1-2 DONE."," - 22:12 Design-data research agent running. Next: build TRISO pin-cell model."," - Modeling decision: compute k_inf(T) of the HTTR average fuel lattice (pin-in-block cell, explicit TRISO double heterogeneity, reflective BC) at 294/600/900/1200 K -> isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T). Absolute criticality is set by frozen control rods in reality, so the transient needs the SHAPE alpha(T), which the reflected lattice captures robustly. Will note leakage/reflector caveat.","+- 22:2x Design data agent returned full report (geometry/enrichment/BP/graphite/VCS/kinetics), sources.md populated, LOFC incident logged.","+- Built model_httr.py (TRISO pin-in-block WS cell, smeared burnable poison, --prompt-only for beta_eff) and transient.py (point kinetics + ANS decay heat + 2-node graphite thermal + VCS). Pipeline validated on synthetic k(T): power collapses in ~6-18 min, core overshoots then cools, recriticality when core returns to Top, self-regulates at low power, temps bounded.","+- Geometry cross-check: HM ~930 kg (matches HTTR ~900 kg U), active-core graphite 13.7 t, reflector ~90 t (~0.9 m responds over 24 h). Responsive graphite thermal mass ~50-70 t.","+- [RUNNING] OpenMC main sweep (BP on, 12000 p x 170 batches) T=294/600/900/1200 K. First temp computing (~20 min/temp). Then: beta_eff (prompt-only @900K), no-BP sensitivity, then transient + sensitivity study."," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01KusWHQrKruPre54M644Nwv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XauDCYyxraXFKhGDkaWH9a","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/root/bench/httr/analyze.py","content":"\"\"\"\nFinal analysis: load OpenMC k_inf(T), compute isothermal temperature coefficient\nalpha(T) with uncertainty, run nominal LOFC transient + sensitivity study, and\nemit results (JSON) and a plot. Consumes runs/main/keff.csv (BP on).\n\"\"\"\nimport json, numpy as np\nimport matplotlib\nmatplotlib.use('Agg')\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nfrom scipy.interpolate import interp1d\nimport transient as TR\n\nRNG = np.random.default_rng(12345)\n\ndef alpha_curve(Tk, kk, sk, Tq):\n    \"\"\"alpha(T)=dk/dT/k^2 [pcm/K] with 1-sigma via Monte Carlo over k points.\"\"\"\n    N = 4000\n    a_samp = np.zeros((N, len(Tq)))\n    dk_samp = np.zeros(N)  # slope 294->1200 overall\n    for i in range(N):\n        kp = kk + RNG.normal(0, 1, len(kk))*sk\n        f = interp1d(Tk, kp, kind='quadratic', fill_value='extrapolate')\n        for j, T in enumerate(Tq):\n            a_samp[i, j] = (f(T+15)-f(T-15))/(30.0*f(T)**2)*1e5\n    return a_samp.mean(0), a_samp.std(0)\n\ndef main():\n    Tk, kk, sk = TR.load_kT('runs/main/keff.csv', bp=1)\n    print(\"k_inf(T):\")\n    for T,k,s in zip(Tk,kk,sk): print(f\"  {T:6.1f} K : {k:.5f} +/- {s:.5f}\")\n    Tq = np.array([400,600,800,1000,1200.])\n    am, asd = alpha_curve(Tk, kk, sk, Tq)\n    print(\"isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T):\")\n    for T,a,s in zip(Tq,am,asd): print(f\"  alpha({T:.0f}K) = {a:7.2f} +/- {s:4.2f} pcm/K\")\n\n    # try beta_eff from prompt-only run if present\n    beta_eff = 0.0065\n    try:\n        import csv\n        with open('runs/kin/keff.csv') as f:\n            rows=list(csv.DictReader(f))\n        kk_full = {float(r['T_K']):(float(r['keff']),float(r['keff_sigma']))\n                   for r in rows if int(r['prompt_only'])==0}\n        kk_pr   = {float(r['T_K']):(float(r['keff']),float(r['keff_sigma']))\n                   for r in rows if int(r['prompt_only'])==1}\n        T0=list(kk_pr.keys())[0]\n        kf,sf=kk_full.get(T0,(None,None)); kp,sp=kk_pr[T0]\n        if kf:\n            beta_eff=1-kp/kf\n            bsig=beta_eff*np.hypot(sf/kf,sp/kp)\n            print(f\"beta_eff (prompt method @ {T0}K) = {beta_eff:.5f} +/- {bsig:.5f}\")\n    except FileNotFoundError:\n        print(\"beta_eff: prompt-only run not found; using 0.0065 (design-basis).\")\n\n    Top = 823.0   # core-avg graphite temp at 9 MW (30%), nominal ~550 C\n    drho, kfun = TR.make_drho(Tk, kk, Top)\n\n    base = dict(Top=Top, P0=9e6, Mc=14000.0, Mr=50000.0, Gcr=6000.0,\n                Q0=0.6e6, Ts=320.0, pexp=1.5, t_op=30*24*3600.0, Lam=1e-3,\n                t_end=5.0*24*3600, S=1e-6)\n    sol, beff = TR.run(base, drho, beta_eff)\n    s0 = TR.summarize(sol, base['P0'], Top, drho)\n    print(\"\\n=== NOMINAL transient ===\")\n    print(f\"  power min (first 30 min): {s0['Pmin_early']/1e3:.2f} kW at {s0['tmin']/60:.1f} min\")\n    print(f\"  peak core temp: {s0['Tc_peak']-273:.0f} C at {s0['tpeak']/3600:.2f} h\")\n    print(f\"  recriticality time: {s0['trec']/3600:.1f} h\" if s0['trec'] else \"  no recriticality\")\n    print(f\"  stabilized fission power: {s0['P_stab']/1e3:.0f} kW ({s0['P_stab']/base['P0']*100:.1f}% of pre-trip 9MW)\")\n\n    # ---------- Sensitivity study ----------\n    print(\"\\n=== SENSITIVITY (recriticality time, stab power, peak Tc) ===\")\n    grid = []\n    for Mr in [25000, 40000, 55000, 70000, 90000]:\n        for Q0 in [0.4e6, 0.6e6, 0.9e6]:\n            for pexp in [1.0, 1.5, 2.0]:\n                for Topv in [773., 823., 873.]:\n                    p = dict(base); p['Mr']=Mr; p['Q0']=Q0; p['pexp']=pexp; p['Top']=Topv\n                    dr,_ = TR.make_drho(Tk, kk, Topv)\n                    so,_ = TR.run(p, dr, beta_eff)\n                    ss = TR.summarize(so, p['P0'], Topv, dr)\n                    grid.append((Mr,Q0,pexp,Topv,\n                                 ss['trec']/3600 if ss['trec'] else np.nan,\n                                 ss['P_stab']/1e3, ss['Tc_peak']-273))\n    grid = np.array(grid)\n    trec = grid[:,4][~np.isnan(grid[:,4])]\n    pstab = grid[:,5]; tcpk = grid[:,6]\n    print(f\"  recriticality time: median {np.median(trec):.1f} h, \"\n          f\"range [{np.percentile(trec,10):.1f}, {np.percentile(trec,90):.1f}] h \"\n          f\"(min {trec.min():.1f}, max {trec.max():.1f})\")\n    print(f\"  stabilized power: median {np.median(pstab):.0f} kW, \"\n          f\"[{np.percentile(pstab,10):.0f}, {np.percentile(pstab,90):.0f}] kW\")\n    print(f\"  peak core temp: median {np.median(tcpk):.0f} C, \"\n          f\"[{np.percentile(tcpk,10):.0f}, {np.percentile(tcpk,90):.0f}] C, max {tcpk.max():.0f} C\")\n\n    # ---------- Plot ----------\n    fig, ax = plt.subplots(2,1, figsize=(8,7), sharex=True)\n    t = sol.t/3600\n    ax[0].plot(t, sol.y[0]/1e6, 'b'); ax[0].set_yscale('log')\n    ax[0].set_ylabel('Fission power (MW)'); ax[0].grid(True, which='both', alpha=.3)\n    ax[0].axhline(9,ls='--',c='gray',lw=.8); ax[0].set_ylim(1e-4,20)\n    if s0['trec']: ax[0].axvline(s0['trec']/3600, ls=':', c='r', label=f\"recrit {s0['trec']/3600:.1f} h\")\n    ax[0].legend(); ax[0].set_title('HTTR LOFC (9 MWt, all circulators trip, no scram, VCS on) — computed')\n    ax[1].plot(t, sol.y[7]-273, 'r', label='core graphite (feedback)')\n    ax[1].plot(t, sol.y[8]-273, 'orange', label='reflector')\n    ax[1].axhline(Top-273, ls='--', c='k', lw=.8, label=f'T_op {Top-273:.0f} C')\n    ax[1].set_ylabel('Temperature (C)'); ax[1].set_xlabel('Time (h)')\n    ax[1].grid(True, alpha=.3); ax[1].legend(); ax[1].set_xlim(0, 120)\n    fig.tight_layout(); fig.savefig('output/lofc_transient.png', dpi=110)\n    print(\"\\nsaved output/lofc_transient.png\")\n\n    out = dict(k_T={float(T):[float(k),float(s)] for T,k,s in zip(Tk,kk,sk)},\n               alpha_T={float(T):[float(a),float(s)] for T,a,s in zip(Tq,am,asd)},\n               beta_eff=float(beta_eff),\n               nominal=dict(Pmin_kW=float(s0['Pmin_early']/1e3),\n                            tmin_min=float(s0['tmin']/60),\n                            Tc_peak_C=float(s0['Tc_peak']-273),\n                            tpeak_h=float(s0['tpeak']/3600),\n                            trec_h=float(s0['trec']/3600) if s0['trec'] else None,\n                            Pstab_kW=float(s0['P_stab']/1e3)),\n               sens=dict(trec_h=[float(np.percentile(trec,10)),float(np.median(trec)),float(np.percentile(trec,90))],\n                         Pstab_kW=[float(np.percentile(pstab,10)),float(np.median(pstab)),float(np.percentile(pstab,90))],\n                         Tcpeak_C=[float(np.percentile(tcpk,10)),float(np.median(tcpk)),float(np.percentile(tcpk,90)),float(tcpk.max())]))\n    json.dump(out, open('output/results.json','w'), indent=2)\n    print(\"saved output/results.json\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2098,"cache_read_input_tokens":130113,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2098},"output_tokens":68,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bf29c1b0-7e93-43a9-86fb-8820c5d1c99e","uuid":"8725a62f-d10a-48df-a4c9-d38a11d0c3be","request_id":"req_011Cce2Q1fYLfuDHXQxqcEmN"}
