transient + 400-sample randomized thermal sensitivity, plot + results.json. Awaiting real k(T).","originalFile":"# PROGRESS — HTTR LOFC prediction\n\nStarted: 2026-07-02 22:08 UTC\n\n## Plan\n1. [DONE] Install OpenMC (0.15.3, conda-forge, MPI) in env `omc`.\n2. [RUNNING] Download ENDF/B-VIII.0 HDF5 nuclear data (~2.5 GB) -> /root/xs/. Has T=250/293.6/600/900/1200/2500 K + graphite S(a,b). ETA ~few min.\n3. [ ] Collect HTTR public DESIGN data (geometry, enrichment zoning, materials, thermal props). Log in sources.md.\n4. [ ] Build OpenMC model: TRISO compact -> fuel rod -> hex fuel block -> full core (reflected) with enrichment zoning.\n5. [ ] Compute k_eff at isothermal T = 300, 600, 900, 1200 K (whole core = fuel+graphite+He same T). Long MC, low sigma.\n6. [ ] Derive isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T) [pcm/K] with statistical uncertainties.\n7. [ ] Build coupled transient model: point kinetics + ANS decay heat + lumped thermal (fuel/graphite/vessel) + VCS heat sink.\n8. [ ] Run LOFC transient: circulator trip at 9 MWt, no scram, rods frozen, VCS on.\n9. [ ] Extract 4 predictions + confidence levels. Write calculation_note.md.\n\n## Status log\n- 22:08 OpenMC installed & verified. XS download launched.\n- 22:11 ENDF/B-VIII.0 downloaded (3.4 GB) + extracted to /root/xs/endfb-viii.0-hdf5/. Confirmed T=294/600/900/1200/2500 K and c_Graphite / c_Graphite_30p / c_U_in_UO2 / c_O_in_UO2 S(a,b). Steps 1-2 DONE.\n- 22:12 Design-data research agent running. Next: build TRISO pin-cell model.\n- Modeling decision: compute k_inf(T) of the HTTR average fuel lattice (pin-in-block cell, explicit TRISO double heterogeneity, reflective BC) at 294/600/900/1200 K -> isothermal temperature coefficient alpha(T). Absolute criticality is set by frozen control rods in reality, so the transient needs the SHAPE alpha(T), which the reflected lattice captures robustly. Will note leakage/reflector caveat.\n- 22:2x Design data agent returned full report (geometry/enrichment/BP/graphite/VCS/kinetics), sources.md populated, LOFC incident logged.\n- Built model_httr.py (TRISO pin-in-block WS cell, smeared burnable poison, --prompt-only for beta_eff) and transient.py (point kinetics + ANS decay heat + 2-node graphite thermal + VCS). Pipeline validated on synthetic k(T): power collapses in ~6-18 min, core overshoots then cools, recriticality when core returns to Top, self-regulates at low power, temps bounded.\n- Geometry cross-check: HM ~930 kg (matches HTTR ~900 kg U), active-core graphite 13.7 t, reflector ~90 t (~0.9 m responds over 24 h). Responsive graphite thermal mass ~50-70 t.\n- [RUNNING] OpenMC main sweep (BP on, 12000 p x 170 batches) T=294/600/900/1200 K. First temp computing (~20 min/temp). Then: beta_eff (prompt-only @900K), no-BP sensitivity, then transient + sensitivity study.\n\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":21,"oldLines":5,"newStart":21,"newLines":8,"lines":[" - 22:2x Design data agent returned full report (geometry/enrichment/BP/graphite/VCS/kinetics), sources.md populated, LOFC incident logged."," - Built model_httr.py (TRISO pin-in-block WS cell, smeared burnable poison, --prompt-only for beta_eff) and transient.py (point kinetics + ANS decay heat + 2-node graphite thermal + VCS). Pipeline validated on synthetic k(T): power collapses in ~6-18 min, core overshoots then cools, recriticality when core returns to Top, self-regulates at low power, temps bounded."," - Geometry cross-check: HM ~930 kg (matches HTTR ~900 kg U), active-core graphite 13.7 t, reflector ~90 t (~0.9 m responds over 24 h). Responsive graphite thermal mass ~50-70 t.","-- [RUNNING] OpenMC main sweep (BP on, 12000 p x 170 batches) T=294/600/900/1200 K. First temp computing (~20 min/temp). Then: beta_eff (prompt-only @900K), no-BP sensitivity, then transient + sensitivity study.","+- [RUNNING] OpenMC main sweep (BP on, 12000 p x 170 batches) T=294/600/900/1200 K (~20-23 min/temp, sigma_k~6e-4). Orchestrator (run_followups.sh) will auto-run beta_eff pair (@900K full+prompt-only) and no-BP sensitivity after.","+- Refined transient.py: 3-node thermal chain core->reflector->vessel->VCS (reports vessel temp). CORRECTED reactivity mapping: Drho_core(T)=1-k_inf(Top)/k_inf(T) and alpha=(1/k)dk/dT (was erroneously /k^2, ~1.5x too small). Fixed decay-heat t->0 divergence (clamp to ~6.3% at 1s). Validated Cp(T) fit (713@300K) and decay curve.","+- Physical picture forming: (1) power collapses in ~1-3 min via negative T-feedback (He voiding worth ~0, so it's pure temperature/Doppler+moderator feedback as 9MW>>passive removal heats the core ~0.3-0.5 K/s); (2) recriticality in a FEW HOURS when core cools back to Top (governed by graphite heat capacity + conduction to the ~100C-cooler reflector/VCS; decay heat drops below passive removal within minutes); (3) stabilizes at the power passive cooling removes at Top ~ few hundred kW (~L0, VCS capacity); (4) temps BOUNDED (peak core overshoot small ~20-50C, vessel VCS-held, no runaway).","+- analyze.py ready: computes k(T), alpha(T)+/-sigma (MC over k), beta_eff (prompt method), nominal transient + 400-sample randomized thermal sensitivity, plot + results.json. Awaiting real k(T)."," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
